fields.title: The Hobbit
fields.review: This movie is so surprising, intense, fierce, magical, stunning and so much more! This movie is so nostalgic since it was released when I was 9 years old.

fields.title: The Maze Runner
fields.review: This movie is so intense, stunning, and little bit of horror. I like how cool the actors are especially when they start running around in the middle of nowhere.

fields.title: Top Gun: Maverick
fields.review: Just.. Amazing. I haven't watched that kind of stunning movie (You know, normal life movies.. no magic, no superpower..) in a long time. The amount of adrenaline and excitement is insane.

fields.title: Knives Out
fields.review: I love reading mystery, riddle, kinda detevtive book since I was a kid. And this movie is just like the visualization of what I read and as exciting as the book.

fields.title: 12 Angry
fields.review: I don't know but people said this movie is great.

fields.title: The Shawshank Redemption
fields.review: Even tho this is a 90's movie, the cinematography is decent and the story is so deep and meaningful. Really recommended it.

fields.title: The Hunger Games
fields.review: Actually, I watched this movie when I was like 10 years old but, I already forgot the movie since I wasn't really interested in movie industry at that time, so let's count that as 'Havent' watched. But, many people said that this movie is amazing so I can't wait to watch this movie again!

fields.title: Mencuri Raden Saleh
fields.review: This is one of the best Indonesian movie I've watched. The story and the cinematography is amazing. But since it was a 2.5 hours long movie, Some part is kinda not as interesting as the others.

fields.title: Avatar
fields.review: This movie is as nostalgic as The Hobbit. I watched this movie when I was 7 years old and this is the best stunning looking movie I've wathced at that time, so insane than the others. The fantasy story is also blew my mind.

fields.title: The King's Speech
fields.review: Really love the story. It was so insightful since the movie told about King George VI who tries to overcome his stammering problem with the help of geniues speech therapist, Lionel Logue.
